"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"95bb58",
"children":[
"Infection with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"herpes simplex virus",
"children":[
"HSV"
]
},
"-1 is the most common cause of sporadic encephalitis in the United States. Fever, altered mental status, headache, seizure, and focal neurologic deficits suggest ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"herpes simplex encephalitis",
"children":[
"HSE"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s3_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1b68a7",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cerebrospinal fluid",
"children":[
"CSF"
]
},
" testing shows lymphocytic pleocytosis and, when necrosis is extensive, erythrocytes. HSV ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"polymerase chain reaction",
"children":[
"PCR"
]
},
" of the CSF allows rapid diagnosis of HSE. Temporal lobe abnormalities on imaging and periodic lateralizing epileptiform discharges on ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electroencephalogram",
"children":[
"EEG"
]
},
" suggest HSE."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7fb69d",
"children":[
"Order HSV PCR in all suspected cases of encephalitis, even if not typical for HSV encephalitis."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"abeaec",
"children":[
"Do not order CSF culture for HSV or serologic testing for HSV."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
